[{"id":39437,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Communication System","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>25</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>20</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>10</mn></math>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<p>Here, modulation index,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#956;</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>A</mi><mi>m</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>A</mi><mi>c</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>20</mn><mn>40</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></p><p>Modulated amplitude <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>&#956;</mi><mi>Ac</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mfrac><mn>40</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (26 Jun Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":39421,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Communication System","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<blockquote><p>Frequencies present in output of square law device</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>f</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi></msub><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><msub><mi>f</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>f</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></msub><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><msub><mi>f</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi></msub><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><msub><mi>f</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>f</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></msub><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>f</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></msub><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><msub><mi>f</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></msub></math></p><p>After passing through band pass filter, frequencies present&nbsp;</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>f</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>f</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></msub><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><msub><mi>f</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi></msub><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><msub><mi>f</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>f</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></msub></math></p><p>Bandwidth of the output signal <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>f</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></msub></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>&#969;</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></msub></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>6</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>28</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>6</mn></msup></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>14</mn></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>MHz</mi></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (29 Jul Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":39476,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Communication System","question":"","options":["$\\left(9+\\sin \\left(2.5 \\pi \\times 10^{5} \\mathrm{t}\\right)\\right) \\sin \\left(2 \\pi \\times 10^{4} \\mathrm{t}\\right) \\mathrm{V}$","$\\left(1+9 \\sin \\left(2 \\pi \\times 10^{4} \\mathrm{t}\\right)\\right) \\sin \\left(2.5 \\pi \\times 10^{5} \\mathrm{t}\\right) \\mathrm{V}$","$\\left(9+\\sin \\left(2 \\pi \\times 10^{4} t\\right)\\right) \\sin \\left(2.5 \\pi \\times 10^{5} \\mathrm{t}\\right) \\mathrm{V}$","$\\left(9+\\sin \\left(4 \\pi \\times 10^{4} t\\right)\\right) \\sin \\left(5 \\pi \\times 10^{5} \\mathrm{t}\\right) \\mathrm{V}$"],"answer":2,"solution":"After analysing the graph we may conclude that\r\n\r\n(i) Amplitude varies as $8-10 \\mathrm{~V}$ or $9 \\pm 1$\r\n\r\n(ii) Two time period as\r\n\r\n$100 \\mu$ s (signal wave) $\\& 8 \\mu$ (carrier wave)\r\n\r\nSo, equation of AM signal is\r\n\r\n$\\left[9 \\pm 1 \\sin \\left(\\frac{2 \\pi t}{T_{1}}\\right) \\sin \\left(\\frac{2 \\pi t}{T_{2}}\\right)\\right]$\r\n\r\n$=\\left[9 \\pm \\sin \\left(2 \\pi \\times 10^{4} \\mathrm{t}\\right)\\right] \\sin \\left(2.5 \\pi \\times 10^{5} \\mathrm{t}\\right) \\mathrm{V}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (11 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":39418,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Communication System","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>kHz</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>20</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>kHz</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>10</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>kHz</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>kHz</mi></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p>We have,&nbsp;</p><p>Message frequency&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>f</mi><mi>m</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>kHz</mi></math>&nbsp;and carrier wave frequency<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>f</mi><mi>c</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>MHz</mi></math><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>2000</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>KHz</mi></math></p><p>The resultant signal will have bandwidth of frequency given by</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\"><mrow><mfenced><mrow><msub><mi>f</mi><mi mathvariant=\"italic\">c</mi></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>f</mi><mi mathvariant=\"italic\">m</mi></msub></mrow></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mrow><msub><mi>f</mi><mi mathvariant=\"italic\">c</mi></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>f</mi><mi mathvariant=\"italic\">m</mi></msub></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mo>[</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>2000</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>-</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>2000</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>]</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>kHz</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>kHz</mi></math>.</p><p>Thus, bandwidth for amplitude modulation is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>10</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>kHz</mi></math>.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (25 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":39464,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Communication System","question":"","options":["Statement I is false but Statement II is true","Both Statement I and Statement II are true","Statement I is true but Statement II is false","Both Statement I and Statement II are false"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>f</mi><mi>m</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>kHz</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>f</mi><mi>c</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>MHz</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1000</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>kHz</mi></math></p><p>Band width <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>f</mi><mi>m</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>kHz</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8756;</mo></math> Side frequencies will be</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>f</mi><mi>c</mi></msub><mo>&#177;</mo><msub><mi>f</mi><mi>m</mi></msub></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>1000</mn><mo>&#177;</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>kHz</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>998</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>kHz</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#38;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>1002</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>kHz</mi></math></p><p>So, statement-I &amp; statement-II both are correct.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (25 Feb Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":39453,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Communication System","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>200</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>kHz</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>500</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>kHz</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>100</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>kHz</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>Bandwidth <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msub><mi>f</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></msub></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>5</mn></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>Hz</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>200</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>kHz</mi></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (25 Jul Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":39501,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Communication System","question":"","options":["vertical type","both vertical and horizontal type","omni directional type","horizontal type"],"answer":0,"solution":"Broadcasting antennas are generally vertical type.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2012 (07 May Online)","image":null},{"id":39430,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Communication System","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<blockquote><p>Maximum range of TV transmission&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>d</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn><mi>R</mi><mi>h</mi></msqrt></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>d</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>6400</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mi>h</mi><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup></msqrt></math>&nbsp;(here,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi></math> in <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math>)</p><p>Maximum area of TV transmission</p><p>Area <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mi>&#960;</mi><msup><mi>d</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>&#960;</mi><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>6400</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">h</mi><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfenced><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi>km</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math></p><p>Now,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>6</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>03</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>100000</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>100</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mi>&#960;</mi><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>6400</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>h</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>6</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>03</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>5</mn></msup></mrow><mrow><mn>10</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mi>&#960;</mi><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>128</mn></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>150</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (25 Jul Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":39457,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Communication System","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi><mo>)-(</mo><mi>iv</mi><mo>), (</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">b</mi><mo>)-(</mo><mi>iii</mi><mo>), (</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi><mo>)-(</mo><mi>ii</mi><mo>), (</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\"