E Main 2021 (18 Mar Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":39407,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Communication System","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1240</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi>km</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3942</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi>km</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4868</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi>km</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1549</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi>km</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<blockquote><p>The given data is&nbsp;</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>H</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>98</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>6400</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>km</mi></math></p><p>The line of sight formula for an antenna is&nbsp;</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>d</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn><mi>R</mi><mi>H</mi></msqrt></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo></math>Area&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mi>&#960;</mi><msup><mi>d</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mi>&#960;</mi><mo mathvariant=\"italic\">&#215;</mo><mn>2</mn><mo mathvariant=\"italic\">&#215;</mo><mi>R</mi><mo mathvariant=\"italic\">&#215;</mo><mi>h</mi></math><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>6400</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>98</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup><mo>&#215;</mo><mi>&#960;</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3940</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi>km</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (08 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":39480,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Communication System","question":"","options":["<math><mn>6.25</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>5</mn></mrow></msup></math>","<math><mn>4.87</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>5</mn></mrow></msup></math>","<math><mn>3.75</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>6</mn></mrow></msup></math>","<math><mn>3.86</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>6</mn></mrow></msup></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"Available signal width <math><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>100</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>c</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>λ</mi></mrow></mfrac></math> <br/><br/> <math><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>100</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>8</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><mn>800</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>9</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac><mi> </mi><mi>H</mi><mi>z</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3.75</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>12</mn></mrow></msup><mi> </mi><mi>H</mi><mi>z</mi></math> <br/><br/>Number of available channels <math><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>3.75</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>12</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><mn>6</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>6</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac></math> <br/><br/> <math><mo>=</mo><mn>6.25</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>5</mn></mrow></msup></math>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (09 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":39412,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Communication System","question":"","options":["Both Statement I and Statement II are correct","Both Statement I and Statement II are incorrect","Statement I is incorrect but Statement II is correct","Statement I is correct but Statement II is incorrect"],"answer":3,"solution":"<p>In amplitude modulation frequency of carrier wave remains unchanged. Minimum size of antenna should be <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math>th of wavelength&nbsp;so that the antenna can sense the variations of the signal properly.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (31 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":39415,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Communication System","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>15</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>10</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>20</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p>Given here,&nbsp;</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>A</mi><mi>c</mi></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>A</mi><mi>m</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>120</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>1</mn></mfenced></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>A</mi><mi>c</mi></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>A</mi><mi>m</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>80</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>2</mn></mfenced></math></p><p>From equation&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mn>1</mn></mfenced></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mn>2</mn></mfenced></math>, we have</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>A</mi><mi>c</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>200</mn><mo>&#8658;</mo><msub><mi>A</mi><mi>c</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>100</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>A</mi><mi>m</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>20</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi></math></p><p>Modulation index&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#956;</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>20</mn><mn>100</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>5</mn></mfrac></math></p><p>Amplitude of each side band</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>A</mi><mi>c</mi></msub><mfrac><mi>&#956;</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>100</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>10</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>volt</mi></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (30 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":39439,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Communication System","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>IV</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>III</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>II</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>IV</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>II</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>III</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>IV</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>II</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>III</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>II</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>III</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>IV</mi></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" style=\"width: 400px;\">\t<tbody>\t\t<tr>\t\t\t<td>&nbsp;</td>\t\t\t<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>List I</strong></td>\t\t\t<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\t\t\t<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>List II</strong></td>\t\t</tr>\t\t<tr>\t\t\t<td>(A)</td>\t\t\t<td>Facsimile</td>\t\t\t<td>(I)</td>\t\t\t<td>Static Document Image</td>\t\t</tr>\t\t<tr>\t\t\t<td>(B)</td>\t\t\t<td>Guided media Channel</td>\t\t\t<td>(II)</td>\t\t\t<td>Optical Fiber</td>\t\t</tr>\t\t<tr>\t\t\t<td>(C)</td>\t\t\t<td>Frequency Modulation</td>\t\t\t<td>(III)</td>\t\t\t<td>\t\t\t<p>Local Broadcast Radio</p>\t\t\t</td>\t\t</tr>\t\t<tr>\t\t\t<td>(D)</td>\t\t\t<td>Digital Signal</td>\t\t\t<td>(IV)</td>\t\t\t<td>Rectangular wave</td>\t\t</tr>\t</tbody></table><p>Hence, the correct answer is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>IV</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>II</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>III</mi></math>.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (25 Jun Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":39456,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Communication System","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>Range <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn><mi>R</mi><mi>h</mi></msqrt></math></p><p>Range (i)<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn><mi>R</mi><mi>h</mi></msqrt></math></p><p>Range (ii) <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn><mi>R</mi><mi>h</mi></msqrt><mo>+</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn><mi>R</mi><mi>h</mi><mo>&#39;</mo></msqrt></math></p><p>where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>20</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#38;</mo><mrow><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>h</mi><mo>&#39;</mo></mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math></p><p>Ans <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msqrt><mn>2</mn><mi>R</mi><mi>h</mi><mo>&#39;</mo></msqrt><msqrt><mn>2</mn><mi>R</mi><mi>h</mi></msqrt></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>100</mn><mo>%</mo><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msqrt><mn>5</mn></msqrt><msqrt><mn>20</mn></msqrt></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>100</mn><mo>%</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>50</mn><mo>%</mo></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (18 Mar Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":39483,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Communication System","question":"","options":["20","10","8","15"],"answer":1,"solution":"Given, modulating frequency $f_m$ $=15 \\mathrm{KHz}$\n$\\therefore \\quad$ Bandwidth of one channel $=2 f_m=30 \\mathrm{kHz}$\n$\\therefore \\quad$ No of channels accommodate\n$$\n=\\frac{300 \\mathrm{kHz}}{30 \\mathrm{kHz}}=10\n$$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2018 (15 Apr Shift 1 Online)","image":null},{"id":39455,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Communication System","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"Maximum amplitude,&nbsp;<br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>A</mi><mi>max</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>A</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>A</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></msub></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><msub><mi>V</mi><mi>max</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>V</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>V</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></msub></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>200</mn><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>V</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></msub><mo>+</mo><mn>160</mn></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>V</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>40</mn></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8756;</mo></math> Peak voltage <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>A</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>40</mn></math><br />Answer is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>40</mn></math>.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (20 Jul Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":39416,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Communication System","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6</mn></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p>As we know, modulation index is given by,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#956;</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msub><mi>A</mi><mrow><mi>m</mi><mi>a</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>A</mi><mrow><mi>m</mi><mi>i</mi><mi>n</mi></mrow></msub></mrow><mrow><msub><mi>A</mi><mrow><mi>m</mi><mi>a</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>A</mi><mrow><mi>m</mi><mi>i</mi><mi>n</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>14</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>14</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (29 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":39414,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Communication System","question":"","options":["A-I, B-II, C-III, D-IV","A-II, B-III, C-IV, D-I","A-IV, B-III, C-I, D-II","A-IV, B-III, C-II, D-I"],"answer":3,"solution":"<p>Attenuation is the loss of signal strength in networking cables or connections.</p><p>Transducers are used in electronic communications systems to convert signals of various physical forms to electronic signals, and vice versa.</p><p>Demodulation is defined as extracting the original information-carrying signal from a modulated carrier wave.</p><p>Repeaters are used to extend transmissions so that the signal can cover longer distances or be received on the other side of an obstruction.</p><p>&nbsp;</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (30 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":39495,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Communication System","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>45</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>km</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>54</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>km</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>55</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>km</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>455</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>km</mi></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>Given,</p><p>Height of transmitting&nbsp;antenna is,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>h</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>50</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math></p><p>Height of receiving antenna is,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>h</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">R</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>32</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math></p><p>Thus,&nbsp;maximum distance for satisfactory communication will be,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>d</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">M</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn><mi>R</mi><msub><mi>h</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></msub></msqrt><mo>+</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn><mi>R</mi><msub><mi>h</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">R</mi></msub></msqrt></math>&nbsp;where&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi></math>&nbsp;is radius of the Earth,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>d</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">M</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn><mi>R</mi><msub><mi>h</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></msub></msqrt><mo>+</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn><mi>R</mi><msub><mi>h</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">R</mi></msub></msqrt><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><msub><mi>d</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">M</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>64</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>5</mn></msup><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>50</mn></msqrt><mo>+</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>64</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>5</mn></msup><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>32</mn></msqrt><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><msub><mi>d</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">M</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>8000</mn><msqrt><mn>10</mn></msqrt><mo>+</mo><mn>6400</mn><msqrt><mn>10</mn></msqrt><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><msub><mi>d</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">M</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>14400</mn><msqrt><mn>10</mn></msqrt><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><msub><mi>d</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">M</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>45536</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>7</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><msub><mi>d</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">M</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>45</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>km</mi></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2014 (09 Apr Online)","image":null},{"id":39432,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Communication System","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>375</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>7</mn></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>75</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>7</mn></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>375</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>8</mn></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>75</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>9</mn></msup></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p>Frequency&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>c</mi><mi>&#955;</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>8</mn></msup></mrow><mrow><mn>1000</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>9</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>14</mn></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>Hz</mi></math></p><p>Band width used for transmission <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>100</mn></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>14</mn></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>Hz</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>12</mn></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>Hz</mi></math></p><p>Number of channels <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>N</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mtext>Total&#160;bandwidth&#160;of&#160;channel</mtext><mo>&#160;</mo></mrow><mrow><mtext>Bandwidth&#160;needed&#160;per&#160;channel</mtext><mo>&#160;</mo></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>6</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>12</mn></msup></mrow><mrow><mn>8</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>3</mn></msup></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>600</mn><mn>8</mn></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>7</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>75</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>7</mn></msup></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (29 Jun Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":39440,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Communication System","question":"","options":["Coaxial cable","Optical fibre","Twisted pair of copper wires","Water"],"answer":1,"solution":"Fiber&nbsp;optics, or optical fiber, refers to the technology that transmits information as light pulses along a glass or plastic fiber. Fiber optics have high efficiency of data transmission.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (25 Jun Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":39445,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Communication System","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>h</mi><mi>r</mi></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>h</mi><mi>t</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>160</mn></math> (Given)<br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>LOS</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">R</mi></msqrt><mfenced><mrow><msqrt><msub><mi>h</mi><mi>r</mi></msub></msqrt><mo>+</mo><msqrt><msub><mi>h</mi><mi>t</mi></msub></msqrt></mrow></mfenced></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>LOS</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn><mi>R</mi></msqrt><mfenced><mrow><msqrt><msub><mi>h</mi><mi>r</mi></msub></msqrt><mo>+</mo><msqrt><mn>160</mn><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>h</mi><mi>r</mi></msub></msqrt></mrow></mfenced></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>dLOS</mi><mrow><mi>d</mi><msub><mi>h</mi><mi>r</mi></msub></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn><mi>R</mi></msqrt><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mn>2</mn><msqrt><msub><mi>h</mi><mi>r</mi></msub></msqrt></mrow></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>160</mn><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>h</mi><mi>r</mi></msub></msqrt></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>h</mi><mi>r</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>h</mi><mi>t</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>80</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>LOS</mo><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn><mi>R</mi></msqrt><mo>(</mo><msqrt><mn>80</mn></msqrt><mo>+</mo><msqrt><mn>80</mn></msqrt><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>6400</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>80</mn></msqrt><mo>=</mo><mn>64</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>km</mi></math>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (31 Aug Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":39477,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Communication System","question":"","options":["1785 and 1715","$178.5$ and $171.5$","$89.25$ and $85.75$","$892.5$ and $857.5$"],"answer":2,"solution":"Equation given<br>$$<br>\\begin{array}{l}<br>\\mathrm{V}(\\mathrm{t})=10\\left[1+0.3 \\cos \\left(2.2 \\times 10^{4}\\right)\\right] \\\\<br>\\sin \\left(5.5 \\times 10^{5} \\mathrm{t}\\right) \\\\<br>=10+1.5\\left[\\sin \\left(57.2 \\times 10^{4} \\mathrm{t}\\right)+\\sin \\left(52.8 \\times 10^{4} \\mathrm{t}\\right)\\right] \\\\<br>\\omega_{\\mathrm{c}}+\\omega_{\\mathrm{w}}=57.2 \\times 10^{4}=2 \\pi \\mathrm{f}_{1}<br>\\end{array}<br>$$<br>$$<br>\\mathrm{f}_{1}=\\frac{57.2 \\times 10^{4}}{2 \\times\\left(\\frac{22}{7}\\right)}=9.1 \\times 10^{4} \\simeq 91 \\mathrm{KHz}<br>$$<br>$$<br>\\omega_{\\mathrm{c}}-\\omega_{\\mathrm{w}}=52.8 \\times 10^{4}<br>$$<br>$$<br>\\mathrm{f}_{2}=\\frac{52.8 \\times 10^{4}}{2 \\times\\left(\\frac{22}{7}\\right)} \\simeq 84 \\mathrm{KHz}<br>$$<br><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/2MM9nZpPivhVAd4drFNV5pSRrw_17zXhcr8Lb24vld4.original.fullsize.png\"><br>Upper side band frequency $\\left(f_{1}\\right)$ is <br>$$<br>\\mathrm{f}_{1}=\\mathrm{f}_{\\mathrm{c}}-\\mathrm{f}_{\\mathrm{w}}=\\frac{52.8 \\times 10^{4}}{2 \\pi} \\approx 85.00 \\mathrm{kHz}<br>$$<br>Lower side band frequency $\\left(\\mathrm{f}_{2}\\right)$ is<br>$$<br>\\mathrm{f}_{2}=\\mathrm{f}_{\\mathrm{c}}+\\mathrm{f}_{\\mathrm{w}}=\\frac{57.2 \\times 10^{4}}{2 \\pi} \\approx 90.00 \\mathrm{kHz}<br>$$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (11 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":39424,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Communication System","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#956;</mi><mo>&#8804;</mo><mn>1</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#956;</mi><mo>&#8805;</mo><mn>1</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#956;</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#956;</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<blockquote><p>The modulation index of an amplitude modulated signal is defined as the measure or extent of amplitude variation about an un-modulated carrier.</p><p>Modulation index is&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#956;</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msub><mi>A</mi><mi>m</mi></msub><msub><mi>A</mi><mi>c</mi></msub></mfrac></math></p><p>To&nbsp;avoid distortion,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#956;</mi><mo>&#8804;</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp;because &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#956;</mi><mo>&#62;</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp;will result in interference between career frequency and message frequency,&nbsp;resulting into distortion.&nbsp;</p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (28 Jul Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":39492,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Communication System","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2000</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>kHz</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mtext>and</mtext><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>1995</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>kHz</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>MHz</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mtext>only</mtext></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2005</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>kHz</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mtext>and</mtext><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>1995</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>kHz</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2005</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>kHz</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>2000</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>kHz</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mtext>and</mtext><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>1995</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>kHz</mi></math>"],"answer":3,"solution":"Frequency of signal wave <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mtext>kH</mtext><mtext>z</mtext><mo>=</mo><mtext mathvariant=\"italic\">f</mtext></math>. Carrier wave frequency <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>MHz</mi></math><br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mn>0</mn><mn>0</mn><mn>0</mn><mo>kHz</mo><mo>=</mo><msub><mtext mathvariant=\"italic\">f</mtext><mtext>c</mtext></msub></math>. The resultant signal maximum frequency<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mtext mathvariant=\"italic\">f</mtext><mo>+</mo><msub><mtext mathvariant=\"italic\">f</mtext><mtext>c</mtext></msub></math><br /><br /><math> <mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mn>5</mn> <mo>+</mo> <mn>2</mn> <mn>0</mn> <mn>0</mn> <mn>0</mn> <mo>kHz</mo> </mrow> </math><br /><br /><math> <mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mn>2</mn> <mn>0</mn> <mn>0</mn> <mn>5</mn> <mo>kHz</mo> </mrow> </math><br /><br />Resultant signal minimum frequency<br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>f</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi></msub><mo>-</mo><mi>f</mi></math><br /><br /><math> <mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mn>2</mn> <mn>0</mn> <mn>0</mn> <mn>0</mn> <mo>-</mo> <mn>5</mn> <mtext>kHz</mtext> </mrow> </math><br /><br /><math> <mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mtext>1995 kHz</mtext></mrow></math>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2015 (04 Apr)","image":null},{"id":39404,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Communication System","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>MHz</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>6</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>kHz</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>MHz</mi><mo>&#160;</mo></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>kHz</mi></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<blockquote><p>The relation between bandwidth and the signal frequency is given by</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>Bandwidth</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>signal</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>frequency</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>1</mn></mfenced></math></p><p>Substitute the values of the known parameter into equation (1) to calculate the required bandwidth.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtable columnalign=\"right center left\" columnspacing=\"0px\"><mtr><mtd><mi>Bandwidth</mi></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#215;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>kHz</mi></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>kHz</mi></mtd></mtr></mtable></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (10 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":39470,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Communication System","question":"","options":["proportional to carrier frequency","independent of both carrier and modulation frequency","inversely proportional to modulation frequency","inversely proportional to carrier frequency"],"answer":3,"solution":"The physical sizes of transmitter and receiver antenna are directly proportional to carrier wave wavelength or inversely proportional to carrier wave frequency.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (09 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":39450,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Communication System","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>A</mi><mi>max</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>A</mi><mi mathvariant=\"italic\">c</mi></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>A</mi><mi mathvariant=\"italic\">m</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>12</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>A</mi><mi>min</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>A</mi><mi>c</mi></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>A</mi><mi>m</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><msub><mi>A</mi><mi mathvariant=\"italic\">c</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>15</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mrow><mo mathvariant=\"italic\">&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"italic\">A</mi></mrow><mi mathvariant=\"italic\">m</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>9</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></p><p>Modulation index <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msub><mi mathvariant=\"italic\">A</mi><mi mathvariant=\"italic\">m</mi></msub><msub><mi mathvariant=\"italic\">A</mi><mi mathvariant=\"italic\">c</mi></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>9</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mstyle><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>15</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mstyle></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (27 Jul Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":39448,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Communication System","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>80</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>km</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>144</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>km</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>57</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>28</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>km</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>45</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>km</mi></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p>The formula of range of the antenna is given by the formula,<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn><mi>R</mi><msub><mi>h</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></msqrt><mo>+</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn><mi>R</mi><msub><mi>h</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></msqrt></math>., here&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi></math>&nbsp;is the radius of the earth then,&nbsp;putting the values, the range <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>57</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>28</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>km</mi></math>.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (26 Aug Shift 2)","image":null}]